						               													<description>The Barons continue their invasion of Lassadar, striking out at the port city of Nem. Raise the call, they attack by sea!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Siege at Nem is a postcard style wargame for 1 or 2 players lasting 25 minutes and is the second game in the 2nd Lassadar game trilogy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This hex and counter style wargame uses a deck of cards (standard or Tarot) + 1d6 for action point (AP) allotment. Action points may be spent to move units, for combat, for spell casting, bombardment of the city or deploying additional units.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game last 7 rounds with the Baron player winning if they can occupy the Citadel Hex in the City of Nem with 1 unit until the end of any turn or if they are able to kill all Lassadar units within the city.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Lassadar player wins if they can sink both of the Baron's Ship units or kill the Baron unit before game end.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Solo rules provided.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
